CONCLUSIONS

Some 45\% of admissions for peptic ulcer bleeding in England and Wales in those aged 60 or more are calculated to be attributable to, or associated with, these accessory risk factors, which, together with those associated with aspirin or other NSAID use will account for over 80\% of predisposing factors to ulcer bleeding.},
