	abstract = {BACKGROUND

  Post-kala-azar dermal leishmaniasis (PKDL) constitutes a parasite reservoir important in the transmission of visceral leishmaniasis (VL). Unacceptable treatment regimens and increasing drug resistance blight control programmes. The success of oral miltefosine in VL prompted a clinical, histopathological and parasitological study of this drug in PKDL.


